<subSubSection id="CA3FDCFBE101563A043EA897EE5FD200" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BB472BA97CD4A197E9756D60148BE61E" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="516056143D543071EBA2E10BF82A8153" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Afrotropical (including Madagascar), Australian, Nearctic, Oriental and Palaearctic regions (Fig. 288). All the species from the Neotropical region described as 
<taxonomicName id="FE0552F465DE1E917E20B4F64F4660A6" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aphthona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphthona" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aphthona</taxonomicName>
should be attributed to different genera (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="106C356FA6A8D18B4C1B58B7A54492B3" author="Konstantinov, AS" journalOrPublisher="Contribution on Entomology" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="237 - 439" title="Handbook of Palearctic Flea Beetle (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Alticinae)." volume="1" year="1996">Konstantinov and Vandenberg 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EB3C1589DB25057135F911DE62A81E3B" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Konstantinov 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="46F0366B6C5FA08DBDFAB7FF8340BE55" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="15EC87793C423B3D1909D2157FD3412C" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF4DDD413EDF88D958BF123E30385651" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Genus mainly associated with 
<taxonomicName id="A5687F3B26A40EB563A66CBDAAE6D9A8" genus="Euphorbiaceae" lsidName="Euphorbiaceae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="genus">Euphorbiaceae</taxonomicName>
, but also with 
<taxonomicName id="ACFFE75FC87FD62DB09F476166F9E7DF" genus="Geraniaceae" lsidName="Geraniaceae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="genus">Geraniaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BA28D0891D0106D0FA887E3525A6497E" genus="Cistaceae" lsidName="Cistaceae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="genus">Cistaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="97EAF0BE036E959861103A84682B018F" genus="Rosaceae" lsidName="Rosaceae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="genus">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FF8EFC362BBF7635ABC7D938772A0CD1" genus="Linaceae" lsidName="Linaceae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="genus">Linaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="34A2CE42CCA0FB75A4545D86407F9E87" genus="Iridaceae" lsidName="Iridaceae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="genus">Iridaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EAB2D5080A5B53B4BCEE2CF3908567D5" genus="Malvaceae" lsidName="Malvaceae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="genus">Malvaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="49B51D0E33B74E69780111A86BD3B6B7" genus="Lythraceae" lsidName="Lythraceae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="genus">Lythraceae</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="262B999739D4D7C14603C01F8E6D7987" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<normalizedToken id="98DEEF89213A97A2EE80C3E7E240FC51" originalValue="Bechyné">Bechyne</normalizedToken>
1955c
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C1F586E007EDD756CE8C5D2355627419" author="Jolivet, P" journalOrPublisher="An essay about the relationships between the leaf-beetles and their food-plants. Backhuys Publishers, Leiden" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" title="Host-plants of Chrysomelidae of the World." year="1995">Jolivet and Hawkeswood 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AAD90321A0185EEED98EC11E97E8336B" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="notes">
<paragraph id="8BC43B6F21FA565B4DD375C634E88CE8" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="05B2C968206A1165F9A5AB1259F8B641" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
About one hundred species are described from Madagascar and Sub-Saharan Africa. There are no important diagnostic characters distinguishing 
<taxonomicName id="E55A1EBDEB077CCC1AA9A08DC8D242D8" authority="Scherer, 1972" authorityName="Scherer" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ethiopia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ethiopia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ethiopia</taxonomicName>
Scherer from 
<taxonomicName id="4A851B89B0CDCF61D9F63FF8A03D93C2" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aphthona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphthona" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aphthona</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, the following new synonymy is proposed: 
<taxonomicName id="96152C7AA090EC2B315AE63D6D658756" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aphthona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphthona" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aphthona</taxonomicName>
Chevrolat, 1836 = 
<taxonomicName id="33CC8DD96C72E2AAEED397C18AAA755A" authority="Scherer, 1972" authorityName="Scherer" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ethiopia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ethiopia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ethiopia</taxonomicName>
Scherer, 1972 syn. n. Type material examined: 
<taxonomicName id="94BC9057D5503A24CB3D1CFD10E6C4BB" authority="Scherer, 1972" authorityName="Scherer" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ethiopia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ethiopia tricolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">Ethiopia tricolor</taxonomicName>
Scherer, holotype ♂ and paratype ♀, &quot;Ethiopia, Agheresalam, 7.6.1963, Linnavuori&quot; (MZHF).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
